A Life Built in Pain

David Goggins grew up in an abusive household filled with violence, fear, and trauma. He struggled in school due to a learning disability and later became overweight, depressed, and directionless. At one point, he weighed nearly 300 pounds, worked a dead-end job, and had no confidence or purpose.

Instead of letting his past define him, Goggins decided to take extreme ownership of his life. He accepted that no one was coming to save him.

